Merge pull request #46 from tablexi/va-allow-ec2-usage-with-computed-ami

Do not specify count for data source aws_ami.mod

Do not specify count for data source aws_ami.mod

If the ami being passed into this module comes as a computed value (for example, because we’re making an `aws_ami_copy` from another image), the count value becomes a computed value, and Terraform does not allow this (so it results in an error).

Since a data source doesn’t create any resources, we don’t need to specify its count—it can always be present, and in the resource `aws_instance` we’ll just use it, or not.

Add new application_load_balancer module

Manage security_group_on_instances via aws_security_group_rule resources

If we specify ingress and egress blocks in the definition of the aws_security_group inline, any rules attached via aws_security_group_rule resources elsewhere would be overwritten when this security group gets applied.

By moving the predefined rules to their own aws_security_group_rule resources, we enable this security group to be used with the application_load_balancer module, which attaches rules to allow web ingress on the instances from the load balancer.

For more details, see the note at the top of https://www.terraform.io/docs/providers/aws/r/security_group.html.

Remove unused variable sg_on_lb_cidr_blocks

sg_on_lb_cidr_blocks is never specified in a call site that uses this module. Hence, it always gets the default value of "0.0.0.0/0", and the count is always 1 for the associated security group rule, so we can just use this value directly and avoid the indirection.

Remove unused variable sg_on_lb_source_ids

sg_on_lb_source_ids is never specified in a call site that uses this module. Hence, the count is always 0 for the associated security group rule, and neither are necessary.
